{
  "texts": [
    "We have seen in Subsection 3.3 Catoni's idea to replace the prior by π -βR for some β > 0, where π -βR is given by Definition 4.2.",
    "This technique is called \"localization of the bound\" by Catoni.",
    "Used in empirical bounds, this trick can lead to tighter bound.",
    "We will study its effect on oracle bounds.",
    "Let us start by providing a counterpart of Theorem 4.3 using this trick (with β = λ/4)."
  ]
}